'Hello World' printNl !

"Send message sublclass: to Object"
Object subclass: #Person.
Person instanceVariableNames: 'balance'.
"Instance instanceVariableNames is a message to the Person object."

Person comment: 'I am the symbiosis of man and machine'.
"Every class in Smalltalk has a description"


Integer comment. "'I am the abstract integer class of the GNU Smalltalk system.  My subclasses'' instances can represent signed integers of various 
sizes (a subclass is picked according to the size), with varying efficiency.'"

Object comment. "I am the root of the Smalltalk class system. All classes in the system are subclasses of me."

Person class extend [
    new [
        | r |
        <category: 'instance creation'>
        r := super new.
        r init.
        ^r
    ]
].
Person extend [
    init [
        <category: 'initialization'>
        balance := 0
    ]
    printOn: stream [
        <category: 'printing'>
        super printOn: stream.
        stream nextPutAll: ' with balance: '.
        balance printOn: stream
    ]
].

russ := Person new.
russ printOn.
